news.title: Haryana CM promise permanent electricity connections to 13 societies
news.para: According to the CM, a policy has been worked upon and supply of connections will start latest by December 21. Khattar said the electrical department will try to recover the money from the builders, and the builders will also call a meeting.

news.title: Mumbai: NCDRC directs Hetali Enterprises to pay Rs 34 lakh to buyers for smaller flat
news.para: The amount includes the market value of Rs 24,650 (2016) per sqft, along with 9% interest. The commission also directed the builder to pay a total of Rs 30 lakh for mental agony and compensation for a delay of eight months in handing over possession and costs of litigation.

news.title: Builders protest Mhada's 'rigged' redevelopment tender for Motilal Nagar
news.para: Mhada has inserted a clause stating only developers with a net worth of not less than Rs 9,000 crore as on March 31, 2021, can qualify. TOI has learned that two top developers, Godrej Properties and Prestige Group, have shot off protest letters to Mhada.

news.title: Gujarat RERA directs Bhanushri Realties to pay compensation to home buyer
news.para: The case involved Gaurav Desai who had purchased a flat in Maruti Amrakunj-2, a scheme floated by Bhanushri Realties, for Rs 30 lakh. According to Desai, he faced delayed possession by five months and use of substandard material in construction.

news.title: Better.com CEO takes time off with immediate effect
news.para: Garg apologized earlier this week for his manner of handling layoffs at the mortgage company after a video of him firing 900 people via a Zoom call went viral on social media.

news.title: China's central bank urges backing for affordable housing in Shanghai
news.para: China's politburo, a top-decision making body, said this week it would support the private housing market to better meet the reasonable needs of home buyers, as regulators make financing changes to ease liquidity strains in property markets.

news.title: Khori village: SC asks Faridabad civic body to address grievances
news.para: ​​A bench of Justices A M Khanwilkar and Dinesh Maheshwari was informed by senior advocate Sanjay Parikh, who was appearing for some petitioners, that persons who have been given provisional allotment of EWS flats are not residing there because it is not habitable.

news.title: Government mulls new urban local body for Amaravati
news.para: The government had already created Amaravati Metropolitan Development Authority on July 30, 2020 by repealing the AP Capital Region Development Authority (APCRDA) Act, 2014.

news.title: Pay Rs 219.5 crore for land taken for pillars: Nagpur civic body to MahaMetro
news.para: The NMC’s estate department has calculated the land value as per ready reckoner rates. As per the survey carried out by the department, MahaMetro has constructed pillars on 32,512.5 sq m land.

news.title: Mohali fixes max sand price at Rs 21 per cubic feet
news.para: Rates of crushers and retailers have been fixed in the three zones of Mubarakpur, Handesra and Majri. Panchayats can get free sand from any mining quarry to carry out development works, said deputy commissioner.

news.title: Rebuild dilapidated houses in Kanmaipatti village: Madras HC
news.para: The government pleader submitted that a plan has been prepared and the work would commence after obtaining approval. He further submitted that alternate arrangements are made for the people to stay in a community hall.

news.title: Builders urge Rajasthan govt to reduce stamp duty in coming budget
news.para: Real estate developers who met Akhil Arora, principal secretary (finance), acknowledged that the government should remove the provision for charging households residing in societies to pay an additional amount for having access to Bisalpur water.

news.title: Mantri Mall in Bengaluru to reopen post high court interim order
news.para: Earlier, during the hearing, counsel for the petitioners claimed a distress warrant was issued for payment of property tax amounting of Rs 6,77,78,286 on February 14, 2020.

news.title: Property tax issues rock Visakhapatnam civic body meet
news.para: Pointing out a particular property tax assessment of a resident and the alleged misdeeds in the revision of the assessment, TDP 39th ward corporator R Srinivasa Rao alleged that irregularities are happening in tax assessments.

news.title: Nashik: Property tax collection target reduced to Rs 130 crore
news.para: Apart from this, the civic body has also reduced the water tax collection target from Rs 60 crore to Rs 50 crore for the current financial year.
